ent companies experienced about the same growth in 1989, but differ ontheir outlook for 1990.andP;  Japanese equipment firms expect 1990 growth to be8.4%, compared with 13.3% this year.andP;  US equipment companies expect sales torise 3.6% in 1990, compared to 15% this year.andP;  When the Japanese and USoutlooks are combined, the forecast averages out at 5% growth for thesemiconductor equipment business in 1990.andO;</TEXT></DOC>